    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''China's Signals on Warming'' (editorial, April 16):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''China's Signals on Warming'' (editorial, April 16):</p>
        <p>As you note, America and China have each been using the other's inaction as an opportune excuse for irresolute responses to the threat of global warming.</p>
        <p>But matters are far too urgent for this ''after you  no, after you'' routine between the two nations to continue. What is reasonable is for our nation to take the lead.</p>
        <p>America remains the world's largest emitter of greenhouse gases, a position that we have held for many decades. Why should we expect a much poorer nation like China, which has only comparatively recently become an industrial power, to make costly economic adjustments unless we set an example first?</p>
        <p>Russ Weiss  Princeton, N.J., April 16, 2007</p>
      </block>
